title: Pre-compaction memory flush fails with 'Incorrect role information' on zai_coding/glm-5
---
When the agent's primary model is zai_coding:glm-5, the pre-compaction memory flush sends
137 messages (system + full conversation history + flush trigger) to the LLM. The provider
returns HTTP 400: {"error":{"code":"1214","message":"Incorrect role information"}}.

This suggests glm-5 has stricter message role requirements than OpenAI-compatible providers
(e.g. it may not accept tool/tool_call roles, or requires strict user/assistant alternation).

The flush fails, compaction proceeds, and context is lost without memory extraction.

Possible fixes:
- Sanitize/convert message roles for non-OpenAI providers before the flush call
- Strip tool_call/tool messages from the flush context (not needed for memory extraction)
- Use a simpler summarization prompt instead of replaying full history with tool roles
- Fall back to a known-compatible model for the flush call

Log:
  [02:37:37.373] INFO  Pre-compaction memory flush: processing 135 messages
  [02:37:37.375] INFO  -> LLM provider=zai_coding model=glm-5 msgs=137 ~46k tok
  [02:37:38.081] WARN  Pre-compaction memory flush failed: Failure("LLM API error (HTTP 400): {"error":{"code":"1214","message":"Incorrect role information"}}")
  [02:37:40.976] INFO  -> LLM provider=zai_coding model=glm-5 msgs=2 ~8k tok